description: Residence 3505, an absolute stunner and the best in "show" for the Spring Market with forever views of Lake Michigan, Maggie Daley, Grant Parks, on center with Buckingham Fountain, Architectural Wall of old and new buildings down Michigan Ave and city skyline scenes, Museum Campus, Soldier Field, the states of Indiana and Michigan and beyond through this unit's floor to ceiling glass curtain walls. Residence 3505 features 9.7" ceilings, brand new 7" wide plank white oak floors throughout this entire home, a foyer that instantly greets you with an irreplaceable and incomparable view of the most coveted parts of the city. Freshly painted, freshly painted, new powder room with large format, rectangular tile by Porcelonsa, in unit full size, stackable washer/dryer, open kitchen concept with culinary vented hood, gas cooktop, built into cabinet oven, recessed microwave, under mount sink with disposal, 1.25" straight edge quartz counters, Flat panel Snaidero cabinets, frosted glass panel upper cabinets, full height glass mosaic kitchen tile backsplash, GE Monogram stainless steel refrigerator, seating area at breakfast comfortable for four. Separate dining room and living space accommodations. Unobstructed views from every area, every window of Residence 3505 with no building neighbors from side to side. Sumptuous and best primary suite out of all of the one bedroom floor plans 340 On the Park has to offer featuring California King bed and plaid of bedside tables, additional bedroom furniture layout, walk in closet and additional linen closet, dual vanity, separate shower, terrazzo shower basin, frameless glass, and soaking tub, Dornbracht plumbing fixtures, Toto toilets, ivory under mount sinks, dressed in all natural composite stone. 340 on the Park is a full amenity building including a 24 hour doorman, onsite management and maintenance, 25th floor amenities include 75' indoor lap pool, whirlpool, sauna, steam rooms, locker rooms, 4,000 square foot gym with Pelotons and other state of the art equipment, Wintergarden, private conference/dining room, complete caterer's kitchen, sun terrace with two gas grills, furniture for dining, lounge chairs for sunning. Dry cleaners, outdoor pet relief area, short cut to Mariano's and the Village Market nearly attached to the building, pedway connection. One garage heated parking space included. Bring on your most discriminating buyer in this market of emaciated inventory. Another project built by Related Midwest, first Leed Certified Residential Building in the City of Chicago and the Gem of Lakeshore East with over $3M in reserve, never having a special assessment, with a reputation that proceeds itself and a location that is second to none in the Lakeshore East community.
